# Quick Integration Guide

## 1. Copy Module

```bash
cp -r teamNeedsAnalysis src/modules/
```

Your structure:
```
src/
└── modules/
    └── teamNeedsAnalysis/
        ├── store/
        ├── types/
        ├── composables/
        ├── views/
        ├── router/
        ├── index.ts
        └── README.md
```

## 2. Register Routes

**File**: `src/router/index.ts`

```typescript
import { teamNeedsAnalysisRoutes } from '@/modules/teamNeedsAnalysis';

const router = createRouter({
  routes: [
    ...teamNeedsAnalysisRoutes,  // ← Add this
  ],
});
```

## 3. Add Navigation (Optional)

```vue
<RouterLink :to="{ name: 'team-needs-dashboard' }">
  Team Needs
</RouterLink>
```

## 4. Configure API Base URL

**File**: `.env`
```env
VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:3000
```

**File**: `src/main.ts` or axios config
```typescript
import axios from 'axios';
axios.defaults.baseURL = import.meta.env.VITE_API_BASE_URL;
```

## Done! 🎉

Navigate to: `http://localhost:5173/team-needs/dashboard`

## Usage Examples

### In a Component

```vue
<script setup lang="ts">
import { useTeamNeedsAnalysisStore } from '@/modules/teamNeedsAnalysis';

const store = useTeamNeedsAnalysisStore();
await store.fetchTeamsNeedsDataTable(2025);
</script>

<template>
  <div>{{ store.averageNeedScore }}</div>
</template>
```

### With Composable

```vue
<script setup lang="ts">
import { useTeamNeedsAnalysis } from '@/modules/teamNeedsAnalysis';

const { 
  store, 
  isLoading, 
  getSeverityColorClass 
} = useTeamNeedsAnalysis();
</script>
```

## Routes Available

- `/team-needs/dashboard` - Main dashboard
- `/team-needs/:teamId` - Team detail view

## Module Structure

```
teamNeedsAnalysis/
├── index.ts          ← Public API (import from here)
├── store/            ← Pinia store
├── types/            ← TypeScript types
├── composables/      ← Helper functions
├── views/            ← Page components
└── router/           ← Route definitions
```

## Key Points

✅ **Self-contained** - Everything in one folder  
✅ **Relative imports** - Internal files use `../`  
✅ **Clean exports** - Import from `@/modules/teamNeedsAnalysis`  
✅ **Portable** - Copy to any project  
✅ **Testable** - Clear boundaries

